The paper deals with statistical properties of dictionaries and their associated Gram matrices, which are topics commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of orthonormal bases and finite harmonic analysis suggests a connection to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the application of the results to the Heisenberg dictionary of chirp like functions suggests a possible connection to statistical inference (cs.SI).
